Crucially, because SDAR offers significantly higher throughput (Study III), \textbf{generating these $k$ samples becomes computationally affordable}.
An SDAR model can generate 32 samples in roughly the same wall-clock time an AR model generates a few, implying that SDAR is not just an efficient inference engine, but an enabler for the "System 2" reasoning paradigm where search replaces raw generation.

